# Audit Platform — <%= appName %>

Track important system actions with full actor context and before/after state.

## Storage backend

**<%= storage %>**

## Recorded fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| User | Actor user id |
| Action | What happened (e.g. `role.update`) |
| Resource | Target entity (e.g. `user:123`) |
| Timestamp | When it occurred |
| IP | Client IP address |
| Device | User agent / device hint |
| Before State | Snapshot before change |
| After State | Snapshot after change |

## Example

```ts
import { auditService, computeStateDiff } from './src/audit/index.js';

await auditService.record(
  { userId: 'admin-1', ip: '127.0.0.1', userAgent: 'curl/8.0' },
  {
    action: 'role.update',
    resource: 'user:42',
    beforeState: { role: 'customer' },
    afterState: { role: 'admin' },
  },
);

const diff = computeStateDiff({ role: 'customer' }, { role: 'admin' });
// { role: { before: 'customer', after: 'admin' } }
```

